  <h2>Food Pairing Guide</h2>

<p>Prosecco's bright acidity, delicate bubbles, and fresh fruit profile create natural flavor bridges with a surprising range of foods. The key lies in understanding how the wine's crisp minerality and effervescence cleanse the palate while its subtle sweetness balances contrasting flavors.</p>

<h3>Classic Venetian Pairings</h3>
<p>In the Veneto region, Prosecco traditionally accompanies <strong>cicchetti</strong> (small plates) featuring ingredients that complement its terroir-driven character. <strong>Prosciutto di San Daniele</strong> creates a perfect marriage—the wine's acidity cuts through the ham's richness while the bubbles lift the meat's savory notes. <strong>Gorgonzola dolce with honey</strong> works beautifully as the wine's minerality balances the cheese's creaminess, while its fruit notes echo the honey's sweetness.</p>

<h3>Versatile Everyday Options</h3>
<p><strong>Fresh mozzarella and tomato salad</strong> showcases Prosecco's versatility—the bubbles enhance the tomatoes' natural acidity while the wine's clean finish doesn't compete with the mozzarella's delicate flavor. <strong>Seafood risotto</strong> is exceptional, as the wine's mineral backbone mirrors the sea's salinity, while effervescence prevents the dish from feeling heavy.</p>

<p><strong>Asian fusion cuisine</strong> creates exciting pairings—try Prosecco with sushi or Vietnamese spring rolls. The wine's crisp profile cuts through rich sauces while its subtle fruit notes complement ginger and lemongrass.</p>

<h3>Special Occasion Selections</h3>
<p>For celebrations, <strong>oysters Rockefeller</strong> with Prosecco DOCG creates an elegant experience—the wine's minerality matches the oysters' brine while bubbles cleanse the palate between rich, creamy bites. <strong>Caviar service</strong> works surprisingly well, especially with Extra Dry styles, where the wine's slight sweetness balances the caviar's salinity without overwhelming its delicate flavor.</p>

<p><strong>Fruit-forward desserts</strong> like peach tart or strawberry shortcake pair beautifully with demi-sec Prosecco, creating a harmonious bridge between the wine's natural fruit character and the dessert's sweetness. The bubbles provide textural contrast that prevents palate fatigue, making each bite as exciting as the first.</p>

